<h1>Accessories Portal - Comprehensive User Manual</h1>

<div class="toc">
    <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><a href="#getting-started">1. Getting Started</a></li>
        <li><a href="#admin-dashboard">2. Admin Dashboard</a></li>
        <li><a href="#counter-dashboard">3. Counter Dashboard</a></li>
        <li><a href="#troubleshooting">4. Support & Troubleshooting</a></li>
    </ol>
</div>

<h2 id="getting-started">1. Getting Started</h2>
<p>Welcome to the <strong>Accessories Portal</strong>! This comprehensive system is designed to streamline inventory management and billing for automobile accessories across multiple counters.</p>

<h3>Accessing the Portal</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Open your web browser and navigate to the portal URL (e.g., http://localhost:5173).</li>
    <li>Enter your registered <strong>Email</strong> and <strong>Password</strong>.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Login</strong>.</li>
    <li>Based on your role, you will be redirected to either the <strong>Admin Dashboard</strong> or the <strong>Counter Dashboard</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="admin-dashboard">2. Admin Dashboard (For Managers & Administrators)</h2>
<p>The Admin Dashboard is the central hub for overseeing the entire operation.</p>

<h3>A. Dashboard Overview</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Summary cards display real-time counts of <strong>Counters</strong>, <strong>Total Inventory items</strong>, and active <strong>Sales Reports</strong>.</li>
    <li>Clicking any card will take you directly to the respective management view.</li>
</ul>

<h3>B. Counter Management</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Access via <strong>"Manage Counters"</strong>.</li>
    <li>View a list of all active counters.</li>
    <li><strong>Add New Counter:</strong> Provide a name and credentials for new staff.</li>
    <li><strong>Edit/Delete:</strong> Update counter names or remove access as needed.</li>
</ul>

<h3>C. Inventory Management</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Excel Upload:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Select the target Counter and the Upload Date.</li>
            <li>Click "Upload Excel" and choose your <em>.xlsx</em> file.</li>
            <li>This is the primary way to bulk-import new stock.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Upload History:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Track every upload session.</li>
            <li><strong>Delete by Date:</strong> If an error occurred during a specific upload, you can delete all items imported on that date.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Global Inventory Slider:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>A visual way to browse stock levels across different vehicle models.</li>
            <li>View specific inventory per Model or per Counter.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Editing & Deleting:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Click on any accessory to edit its quantity or price.</li>
            <li>Use the "Trash" icon to remove an item from the system.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Stock Transfer:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Move items from one counter to another.</li>
            <li><strong>Transfer Single:</strong> Move a specific quantity of one item instantly.</li>
            <li><strong>Transfer Cart:</strong> Add multiple items to a "Transfer Cart" and move them all at once to a destination counter.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>D. System Reports & Billing</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>System Reports Slider:</strong> 
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ledger:</strong> View outstanding (debit) and paid (credit) balances per counter.</li>
            <li><strong>Revenue Report:</strong> Detailed revenue and item sales performance per counter.</li>
            <li><strong>Inventory Report:</strong> Track surplus (&gt; 5) and shortage (&le; 5) items across all counters.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Bill Monitoring:</strong> View all generated bills. Click any bill to see the full itemized breakdown, payment method, and balance status.</li>
    <li><strong>Date Filtering:</strong> Use the date range filter to view performance for specific days, weeks, or months.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="counter-dashboard">3. Counter Dashboard (For Sales Staff)</h2>
<p>The Counter Dashboard is optimized for fast sales and local stock tracking.</p>

<h3>A. Making a Sale (Generating a Bill)</h3>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Search:</strong> Use the Global Search bar to find an accessory by Name or Code.</li>
    <li><strong>Select Model:</strong> Alternatively, use the "Select Model" dropdown to see all accessories available for a specific vehicle (e.g., Elevate, City).</li>
    <li><strong>Add to Cart:</strong> Click the "Add to Cart" button on an item.</li>
    <li><strong>Set Quantity:</strong> In the popup, enter the quantity being sold.</li>
    <li><strong>Review Cart:</strong> Click the "CART" button at the top right to review items, adjust quantities, or remove items.</li>
    <li><strong>Checkout:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Enter Customer Name and Mobile Number.</li>
            <li>Select Payment Method (Cash, UPI, Bank Transfer, or Card).</li>
            <li>Enter Amount Paid (if partial payment).</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Generate:</strong> Click "Generate Bill". The system will assign a unique bill number (e.g., INV-001) and update the stock levels automatically.</li>
</ol>

<h3>B. Inventory Monitoring</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Shortage:</strong> View items with stock level &le; 5 units. Ensure you request refills or transfers for these items.</li>
    <li><strong>Surplus:</strong> View well-stocked items (&gt; 5 units).</li>
</ul>

<h3>C. Previous Bills</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Access via "Previous Bills" card.</li>
    <li>Search and filter your counter's history by date, accessory name, or payment method.</li>
    <li>View details of any past transaction by clicking the row.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="troubleshooting">4. Support & Troubleshooting</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Login Issues:</strong> Ensure CAPS LOCK is off. If you forget your password, contact the Administrator.</li>
    <li><strong>Data Errors:</strong> If inventory counts seem wrong, check the "Upload History" in the Admin panel to verify the last Excel import.</li>
    <li><strong>Printing:</strong> After generating a bill, use the browser's print function (Ctrl+P) to provide a copy to the customer.</li>
</ul>

<p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 50px;"><em>End of Document</em></p>

</body>
</html>
